---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const EFFECTIVE_DATE = "March 5, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — ShelfSkin"
  description="Privacy Policy for ShelfSkin: Scan & Track Skincare. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your information."
  active="privacy"
>
  <header class="policy-header">
    <span class="badge">Effective Date: {EFFECTIVE_DATE}</span>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy describes how AOHSTD ("we", "our", or "us") collects,
      uses, processes, and discloses information when you use the ShelfSkin
      mobile application and related websites (collectively, the "Service").
    </p>
    <p>
      By accessing or using the Service, you acknowledge that you have read
      and understood this Privacy Policy.
    </p>
  </header>

  <!-- ─── SUMMARY ─── -->
  <div class="summary" style="margin-top: 18px;">
    <div class="head">
      <svg width="18" height="18" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M12 2a10 10 0 100 20 10 10 0 000-20zm1 14h-2v-2h2v2zm0-4h-2V7h2v5z" fill="currentColor"/>
      </svg>
      Quick overview
    </div>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="item">
        <div>
          <strong>Camera &amp; images</strong>
          <span>Used only for product scanning. Photos are sent to a third-party AI service for ingredient recognition, then discarded.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="item">
        <div>
          <strong>Skin profile</strong>
          <span>Skin type, goals, and preferences are stored on your device to personalize tips and conflict detection.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="item">
        <div>
          <strong>Product shelf</strong>
          <span>Products, ingredients, and expiry dates you add are stored on your device.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="item">
        <div>
          <strong>Analytics</strong>
          <span>We use Firebase for crash reports and anonymous usage analytics. No personal skincare data is sent to analytics.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="item">
        <div>
          <strong>No data sales</strong>
          <span>We never sell your personal information to advertisers or data brokers.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="item">
        <div>
          <strong>You control your data</strong>
          <span>Delete all data at any time from Profile → Delete All Data inside the app.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── DISCLAIMER ─── -->
  <div class="note" style="margin-top: 18px;">
    <strong>ShelfSkin is not a medical application.</strong> All information
    provided by the Service — including ingredient analysis, conflict detection,
    and skincare tips — is generated using artificial intelligence and general
    skincare knowledge. It is intended for educational purposes only and should
    not be considered medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. Results are not
    guaranteed to be accurate or complete. Always consult a qualified
    dermatologist or healthcare provider for skin concerns.
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 1. INFORMATION WE COLLECT ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="collect">
    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <div class="card">

      <p><b>A) Technical and Usage Information</b></p>
      <p>
        We automatically collect certain technical information necessary to
        operate and improve the Service, including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Device model and device identifiers</li>
        <li>Operating system version</li>
        <li>Application version</li>
        <li>Crash logs and diagnostics data</li>
        <li>Performance metrics</li>
        <li>Feature usage events (e.g., number of scans, screens visited)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This information is processed by <b>Google Firebase</b> (Analytics and Crashlytics)
        on our behalf. Firebase may assign anonymous identifiers to your device.
        No personal skincare data (such as your skin type, products, or ingredients)
        is included in analytics data.
      </p>

      <p><b>B) Camera and Image Data</b></p>
      <p>
        ShelfSkin uses your device camera to scan product ingredient lists and
        barcodes. When you initiate a scan:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          The captured image is sent to a <b>third-party AI processing service
          (Anthropic)</b> solely to identify and extract ingredient information
          from the product label.
        </li>
        <li>
          Images are transmitted over encrypted connections and are processed
          in real time to return scan results.
        </li>
        <li>
          We do not store scanned images on our servers after processing is
          complete. Anthropic's data handling is governed by their own
          <a class="link" href="https://www.anthropic.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">privacy policy</a>.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Camera access is requested only when you actively use the scan feature.
        You can revoke camera permission at any time through your device settings.
      </p>

      <p><b>C) Profile and Preference Data</b></p>
      <p>
        During onboarding and in your profile settings, you may provide
        information such as:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Skin type (e.g., oily, dry, combination, sensitive)</li>
        <li>Skincare goals (e.g., acne, aging, hyperpigmentation)</li>
        <li>Routine level (simple, moderate, advanced)</li>
        <li>Monthly skincare budget range</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This information is stored <b>locally on your device</b> and is used
        solely to personalize tips, conflict detection, and insights within the
        app. It is not uploaded to our servers or shared with third parties.
      </p>

      <p><b>D) Product and Shelf Data</b></p>
      <p>
        The Service allows you to build a digital shelf of skincare products.
        This includes:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Product names and brands</li>
        <li>Ingredient lists</li>
        <li>Expiry and Period After Opening (PAO) dates</li>
        <li>Product categories and application zones (e.g., face, body)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This data is stored <b>locally on your device</b> and is used to provide
        ingredient conflict detection, synergy identification, expiry tracking,
        and personalized recommendations. It is not uploaded to our servers or
        shared with third parties.
      </p>

      <p><b>E) Subscription and Billing Information</b></p>
      <p>
        ShelfSkin offers optional premium features via in-app subscription.
        Payments are processed entirely by the platform provider (Google Play
        or Apple App Store). We do not collect or store payment card details.
      </p>
      <p>
        We may receive limited information from the platform provider, such as
        subscription status and expiration date, in order to enable or manage
        paid features.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 2. HOW WE USE INFORMATION ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="use">
    <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>We use the information described above to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Provide product scanning, ingredient analysis, and conflict detection</li>
        <li>Personalize tips and insights based on your skin profile and products</li>
        <li>Track product expiry dates and send reminders</li>
        <li>Improve app performance, stability, and user experience</li>
        <li>Monitor and prevent fraud, abuse, or security incidents</li>
        <li>Verify subscriptions and manage premium features</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 3. DISCLOSURE ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="sharing">
    <h2>3. Disclosure of Information</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        We do not sell personal information to advertisers or data brokers.
      </p>
      <p>We may share limited information with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <b>Anthropic</b> — scanned product images are sent to Anthropic's API
          for ingredient recognition. Images are processed in real time and are
          not retained by us after processing.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Google Firebase</b> — anonymous device and usage analytics, crash
          reports, and diagnostics.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Platform providers</b> (Google Play or Apple App Store) — for billing
          and subscription processing.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Authorities</b> — if required by law or to protect legal rights.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 4. DATA STORAGE ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="storage">
    <h2>4. Data Storage and Retention</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        Your skin profile, product shelf, and preference data are stored
        <b>locally on your device</b>. We do not maintain a copy of this data
        on our servers.
      </p>
      <p>
        Technical and analytics data processed by Firebase is retained in
        accordance with Google's data retention policies. We configure retention
        periods to the minimum necessary for analytics purposes.
      </p>
      <p>
        Scanned images sent to Anthropic for ingredient recognition are
        processed in real time and are not stored by us after the scan result
        is returned.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 5. YOUR RIGHTS & DATA DELETION ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="rights">
    <h2>5. Your Rights and Data Deletion</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to access, correct,
        delete, or restrict the processing of your personal information.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>In-app deletion:</b> You can delete all personal and product data
        stored by ShelfSkin at any time by going to
        <span class="kbd">Profile → Delete All Data</span>.
        Upon deletion, all locally stored data (skin profile, product shelf,
        preferences) is permanently removed from your device.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Analytics data:</b> Anonymous analytics and diagnostics data
        collected by Firebase cannot be linked to individual users. Because
        this data is anonymous and aggregated, it cannot be attributed to or
        deleted for a specific user. It is retained in accordance with
        Google's standard data retention policies.
      </p>
      <p>
        For any privacy-related questions, please contact us at
        <a class="link" href="mailto:support@aohstd.com">support@aohstd.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 6. DATA SECURITY ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="security">
    <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to
        safeguard information against unauthorized access, alteration,
        disclosure, or destruction.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Images sent for scanning are transmitted over encrypted (HTTPS) connections.</li>
        <li>Local data on your device is protected by your device's own security mechanisms.</li>
        <li>Analytics data is processed by Firebase using Google's security infrastructure.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        However, no method of transmission or storage can be guaranteed to be
        completely secure.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 7. INTERNATIONAL TRANSFERS ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="international">
    <h2>7. International Data Transfers</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        Scanned images are processed by Anthropic, whose servers may be located
        in the United States. Analytics data is processed by Google Firebase,
        whose infrastructure spans multiple countries. By using the Service, you
        consent to such transfers where permitted by applicable law.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 8. CHILDREN ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="children">
    <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        ShelfSkin is not directed to children under the age of 13 (or the
        equivalent minimum age in your jurisdiction). We do not knowingly
        collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has
        provided us with personal information, please contact us so we can
        delete it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 9. CHANGES ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="changes">
    <h2>9. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The updated
        version will be indicated by the revised Effective Date above. We
        encourage you to review this page periodically.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 10. CONTACT ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="contact">
    <h2>10. Contact Information</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        If you have questions regarding this Privacy Policy or wish to exercise
        your data rights, please contact:
      </p>
      <p>
        <a class="link" href="mailto:support@aohstd.com">support@aohstd.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <footer class="footer">
    <div class="links">
      <a href="/shelfskin">ShelfSkin</a>
      <a href="/shelfskin/terms">Terms</a>
      <a href="/privacy">AOHSTD Privacy</a>
      <a href="mailto:support@aohstd.com">support@aohstd.com</a>
    </div>
    <small>© {new Date().getFullYear()} AOHSTD</small>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
